verses.text: And the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came unto me, saying ,

Son of man , prophesy against the shepherds of Israel , prophesy , and say unto them, Thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd* unto the shepherds ; Woe \add be\add* to the shepherds of Israel that do feed themselves! should not the shepherds feed the flocks ?
Ye eat the fat , and ye clothe you with the wool , ye kill them that are fed : \add but\add* ye feed not the flock.

The diseased have ye not strengthened , neither have ye healed that which was sick , neither have ye bound up \add that which was\add* broken , neither have ye brought again that which was driven away , neither have ye sought that which was lost ; but with force and with cruelty have ye ruled them.
And they were scattered , because \add there is\add* no shepherd : and they became meat to all the beasts of the field , when they were scattered.\f + \fr 34.5 \ft because…: or, without a shepherd\f*
My sheep wandered through all the mountains , and upon every high hill : yea, my flock was scattered upon all the face of the earth , and none did search or seek \add after them\add*. \p
¶ Therefore, ye shepherds , hear the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*;

\add As\add* I live , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*, surely because my flock became a prey , and my flock became meat to every beast of the field , because \add there was\add* no shepherd , neither did my shepherds search for my flock , but the shepherds fed themselves, and fed not my flock ;\f + \fr 34.8 \ft because…: or, without a shepherd\f*
Therefore, O ye shepherds , hear the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*;

Thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; Behold, I \add am\add* against the shepherds ; and I will require my flock at their hand , and cause them to cease from feeding the flock ; neither shall the shepherds feed themselves any more; for I will deliver my flock from their mouth , that they may not be meat for them. \p
¶ For thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; Behold, I, \add even\add* I, will both search my sheep , and seek them out.

As a shepherd seeketh out his flock in the day that he is among his sheep \add that are\add* scattered ; so will I seek out my sheep , and will deliver them out of all places where they have been scattered in the cloudy and dark day.\f + \fr 34.12 \ft As…: Heb. According to the seeking\f*

And I will bring them out from the people , and gather them from the countries , and will bring them to their own land , and feed them upon the mountains of Israel by the rivers , and in all the inhabited places of the country.

I will feed them in a good pasture , and upon the high mountains of Israel shall their fold be: there shall they lie in a good fold , and \add in\add* a fat pasture shall they feed upon the mountains of Israel.
I will feed my flock , and I will cause them to lie down , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*.

I will seek that which was lost , and bring again that which was driven away , and will bind up \add that which was\add* broken , and will strengthen that which was sick : but I will destroy the fat and the strong ; I will feed them with judgment. \p

And \add as for\add* you , O my flock , thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; Behold, I judge between cattle and cattle , between the rams and the he goats.\f + \fr 34.17 \ft cattle: Heb. small cattle of lambs and kids\f*\f + \fr 34.17 \ft he goats: Heb. great he goats\f*

\add Seemeth it\add* a small thing unto you to have eaten up the good pasture , but ye must tread down with your feet the residue of your pastures ? and to have drunk of the deep waters , but ye must foul the residue with your feet ?
And \add as for\add* my flock , they eat that which ye have trodden with your feet ; and they drink that which ye have fouled with your feet. \p
¶ Therefore thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd* unto them; Behold, I, \add even\add* I, will judge between the fat cattle and between the lean cattle.
Because ye have thrust with side and with shoulder , and pushed all the diseased with your horns , till ye have scattered them abroad ;
Therefore will I save my flock , and they shall no more be a prey ; and I will judge between cattle and cattle.
And I will set up one shepherd over them, and he shall feed them, \add even\add* my servant David ; he shall feed them, and he shall be their shepherd.

And I the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* will be their God , and my servant David a prince among them; I the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* have spoken \add it\add*.
And I will make with them a covenant of peace , and will cause the evil beasts to cease out of the land : and they shall dwell safely in the wilderness , and sleep in the woods.
And I will make them and the places round about my hill a blessing ; and I will cause the shower to come down in his season ; there shall be showers of blessing.

And the tree of the field shall yield her fruit , and the earth shall yield her increase , and they shall be safe in their land , and shall know that I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, when I have broken the bands of their yoke , and delivered them out of the hand of those that served themselves of them.
And they shall no more be a prey to the heathen , neither shall the beast of the land devour them; but they shall dwell safely , and none shall make \add them\add* afraid.

And I will raise up for them a plant of renown , and they shall be no more consumed with hunger in the land , neither bear the shame of the heathen any more.\f + \fr 34.29 \ft of renown: or, for renown\f*\f + \fr 34.29 \ft consumed: Heb. taken away\f*

Thus shall they know that I the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* their God \add am\add* with them, and \add that\add* they, \add even\add* the house of Israel , \add are\add* my people , saith the Lord 
d \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*
d*.
And ye my flock , the flock of my pasture , \add are\add* men , \add and\add* I \add am\add* your God , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*.
